<section class="section section-alt">
  <div class="container-narrow">
    <div class="section-header center reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow" style="justify-content:center;">Workbook FAQ</span>
      <h2>A few things people ask first.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="reveal">
      <details class="accordion-item" name="workbook-faq">
        <summary class="accordion-trigger"><span>Do I need to be a good writer to use this?</span>{{ plus() }}</summary>
        <div class="accordion-panel-content">Not at all. The workbook is built for people who know how they feel but haven't found the words yet — that's most of us. Every section breaks the process into small, manageable steps.</div>
      </details>
      <details class="accordion-item" name="workbook-faq">
        <summary class="accordion-trigger"><span>Will this work for a non-traditional wedding?</span>{{ plus() }}</summary>
        <div class="accordion-panel-content">Yes. The prompts focus on your relationship and your story, not on a specific tradition or format, so they adapt naturally to any couple, culture, or ceremony style.</div>
      </details>
      <details class="accordion-item" name="workbook-faq">
        <summary class="accordion-trigger"><span>What if I get stuck partway through?</span>{{ plus() }}</summary>
        <div class="accordion-panel-content">That's normal, and the workbook is designed for it — you can skip ahead and come back. If you'd like a person to help you push through, our <a href="/services/">Review &amp; Refine service</a> picks up right where the workbook leaves off.</div>
      </details>
      <details class="accordion-item" name="workbook-faq">
        <summary class="accordion-trigger"><span>How is this different from just Googling "wedding vow examples"?</span>{{ plus() }}</summary>
        <div class="accordion-panel-content">Example vows are written for someone else's relationship. This workbook doesn't give you lines to borrow — it gives you a process for finding your own, so what you say actually sounds like you.</div>
      </details>
    </div>
    <div class="text-center reveal" style="margin-top: var(--space-lg);">
      <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/faq/">Read All FAQs</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container-narrow text-center reveal">
    <p class="guiding-principle">"You already have the feelings. We simply help you express them."</p>
